                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17294512" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 3 Mar 2021 12:56:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;try with 3.8.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17294513" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 3 Mar 2021 12:58:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It smells like there is some code to stop http server in doStop of the as2 component that is not called.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17294515" author="ancosen" created="Wed, 3 Mar 2021 12:59:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it could be something related to windows too.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17294523" author="pswid" created="Wed, 3 Mar 2021 13:17:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;with 3.8.0 I have the same error.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17294526" author="ancosen" created="Wed, 3 Mar 2021 13:24:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;on the endpoint there is an as2ServerConnection. It is created but never released.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17294530" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 3 Mar 2021 13:37:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah I have looked too, and can see the same problem. Have a fix to stop all connections when the component is being stopped. Push a commit in a moment&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
